@startuml AI Data Block
!define RECTANGLE class
!define AGENT node

RECTANGLE "User" as User {
    :Submit query;
}

RECTANGLE "User Query" as Q
RECTANGLE "Predefined Prompt (Specific or Complex)" as P
RECTANGLE "Data Collection and Ingestion" as A
RECTANGLE "Data Preprocessing" as B
RECTANGLE "Data Transformation" as C
RECTANGLE "Model Training / Existing Model Use" as D
RECTANGLE "Model Evaluation" as E
RECTANGLE "Deployment for Real-Time Interaction" as F
RECTANGLE "Continuous Learning and Feedback" as G
RECTANGLE "Upload and Process Documents" as H
RECTANGLE "Temporary Processing and Query Answering" as I
RECTANGLE "Persistent Learning Path" as J
RECTANGLE "Update Knowledge Base / Index" as K
RECTANGLE "Output: Answers / Recommendations / Comparisons" as O

AGENT "AI Agents" {
    User --> Q
    Q --> P
    P --> A
    A --> B
    B --> C
    C --> D
    D --> E
    E --> F
    F --> G
    F --> H
    H --> I
    H --> J
    J --> K
    K --> G
    I --> O
}

note right of "AI Agents"
    AI Agents manage and coordinate the entire workflow,
    overseeing each step in the process to ensure smooth
    operation and response generation.
end note

note left of Q : User submits query
note right of P : Prompts guide AI processing
note right of A : Tools: Apache Kafka, Logstash
note right of B : Tools: Pandas, NLTK, OpenRefine
note right of C : Tools: Scikit-learn, Gensim, FastText
note right of D : Tools: TensorFlow, PyTorch, RAG
note right of E : Evaluation: TensorBoard, Metrics
note right of F : Deployment: Flask, Docker
note right of H : Tools: Haystack, LangChain
note right of J : Indexing: Elasticsearch, FAISS
note right of K : Storage: Neo4j, Redis

note top of G : Updates models and retrains with feedback
note top of I : Executes prompt-based responses
note top of O : Presents summarized results

@enduml
